# ==============================================================================
# PROJECT EXCLUSIONS (.gitignore)
# ==============================================================================
# This file tells Git which files or folders to completely ignore. 
# This keeps our cloud repository clean, lightweight, and secure.
# ==============================================================================

# 🌐 Local Browser Infrastructure
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# We use a portable, self-contained browser setup so the scraper runs out-of-the-box.
# We exclude these heavy, system-specific binaries to avoid crashing GitHub's 
# file size limits and causing cross-platform errors.
FirefoxPortable/
geckodriver.exe

# 🐍 Python Runtime Caches
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are temporary background files generated by Python during script execution.
# They change constantly and regenerate automatically, so Git doesn't need to track them.
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# 📊 Data Pipeline Storage (The Whitelist Strategy)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Websites generate heavy logs and local databases when scraped. We want to keep 
# our workspace tidy while still preserving our foundational mapping data.

# Step 1: Tell Git to ignore absolutely everything inside the data/ folder
data/*

# Step 2: Use the exclamation mark (!) to create a strict exemption rule.
# We MUST track this specific file so the dashboard has the seed coordinates 
# it needs to render the world map.
!data/city_coordinates.csv